# .cursorrules — ReKnew AI-SDLC Platform

## Project

This is a Python project that extends Delegate (an AI agent orchestrator). ReKnew code is in `reknew/`. Do not modify `delegate/` unless the spec explicitly instructs it.

## Stack

- Python 3.12+ with type hints
- FastAPI for API server
- asyncio for daemon concurrency
- PyGithub for GitHub API
- anthropic SDK for LLM calls
- pytest + pytest-asyncio for tests
- dataclasses + Enum for data models
- PyYAML for config
- subprocess for git operations and agent spawning

## Rules

- Type hints on all function signatures
- Google-style docstrings on all public methods
- f-strings only (no .format())
- Use pathlib.Path not os.path
- Use subprocess.run not os.system
- async/await for all I/O in daemon code
- Catch specific exceptions, never bare except
- Log with logging module (named loggers per module)
- Config values from reknew.yaml, never hardcoded
- Tests mock external APIs (GitHub, Anthropic) — never make real API calls in tests

## File naming

- Snake case for all Python files
- One class per file for major components
- __init__.py in every package directory
- Tests named test_{module}.py

## Git

- Branch naming: reknew/task/T{number}
- Only the daemon creates worktrees, branches, merges
- Agents write code and commit inside worktrees only
